covered: Valid Payload: TC01–TC03 cover creation with valid payloads
Invalid Payload: TC05, TC06, TC12, TC15 cover malformed JSON, missing required fields, empty payload, and injection attempts
Duplicate Submission: TC13 (and regression TC19) cover duplicate handling
Large Payloads: TC11 tests maximum field sizes
Validation/Authorization: TC04 (missing required header) and TC08 (invalid header value types) cover input/header validation; TC09 covers unauthorized access
Server Error Handling: TC10 demonstrates service unavailable (503) as a server error
Integration: TC20 verifies retrieval of created account via GET
Edge cases for inputs: TC07 (extra fields), TC16 (partial input), and TC17 (additional headers) cover resilience to non-ideal inputs
gaps: Rate Limiting: No tests for 429 Too Many Requests (POST throttling)
Caching Behavior: No tests for ETag/Cache-Control headers on POST responses or caching semantics on GET
Forbidden Access: No test for 403 Forbidden (only 401 Unauthorized covered)
Internal Server Error: No explicit 500 Internal Server Error test (503 used in TC10)
Field-level data validation: Not exhaustive for domain-specific fields (e.g., email format, numeric ranges)
recommendations: Add rate-limiting tests (429) for POST /1.0/kb/accounts, including under high concurrency scenarios (to exercise TC18-like conditions)
Add caching/header validation tests (ETag, Cache-Control) for POST responses and ensure GET responses expose proper caching headers
Add explicit 403 Forbidden tests to exercise complete authorization scenarios
Add explicit 500 Internal Server Error tests to validate system resilience under database/service failures
Expand field-level validations in the Account object (e.g., email format, numeric constraints) and document required formats for test data
Enhance security tests to cover additional input validation beyond XSS (e.g., SQL-related patterns)
